Garage in four stages
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex guarantees that the user receives a devis in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the spare part, create a devis and generate it.
The ease of use is an essential part of these systems, especially to convince the older professionals who, in a more or less extent, are reactive to the use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 tourists, 109 all-terrainers, 137 motorcycles, 78 wagons and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it, a computer and an Internet connection are required.
Once the model to be repaired is identified by its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the required piece is selected.
The user can include variables such as the workforce price, increases or discounts, and then he can print the devis to return it to the customer.
AudaTaller is not an assessment tool like AudaPlus, but a reference catalogue.
